#week-title("One", "Designing the Full-Year Mineral Almanac")

=== Core Teaching

At the Adept level, astrological timing is not merely a suggestion — it is a
structural element of the Work. Year Two Month 5 introduced the personal
alchemical calendar as a general framework. Year Three Month 5 deepens this
into a specific mineral almanac: a working calendar designed for the particular
demands of the metallic and mineral work now underway.

The mineral work operates at slower timescales than the vegetable work, which
means the astrological timing framework must extend correspondingly further. A
major mineral preparation begun under Saturn in 2025 will not conclude until
2026 or 2027. The almanac must therefore take a multi-year view, not merely a
single year.

*Designing the mineral almanac.* The following elements structure it:

- *Saturn cycles:* Saturn's transit through each sign takes approximately
  two and a half years. Saturn-ruled operations (lead work, antimony work,
  long cold digestions) are most naturally begun when Saturn is strong in the
  chart — in its own signs (Capricorn, Aquarius) or in dignity.
- *Jupiter cycles:* Jupiter transits each sign in approximately one year.
  Jupiter-ruled operations (tin work, expansion and multiplication of a
  preparation) align with Jupiter's favorable position.
- *Lunar monthly cycle:* As in the vegetable work — waxing for dissolving and
  extracting, waning for calcination and fixation — but now with attention to
  what sign the Moon occupies: earth signs for solidifying and crystallising;
  water signs for Via Humida dissolutions; fire signs for calcination.
- *Solar ingresses:* The Sun's entry into each cardinal sign (Aries, Cancer,
  Libra, Capricorn) marks the four seasonal thresholds, which the tradition
  regards as significant moments for reviewing and re-orienting major works.
- *Personal natal factors:* The student's own Saturn return or Saturn transits
  to natal positions are particularly significant for mineral work.

=== Topics This Week

- Extending the alchemical calendar to multi-year mineral timescales
- Saturn and Jupiter cycles as the primary mineral timing framework
- Lunar sign positions for mineral operations
- Solar ingresses as seasonal review thresholds
- Natal Saturn transits and their significance for mineral work

#inner-work[
  *The Mineral Almanac as Declaration*

  Designing the mineral almanac is itself an operative act: it is the
  practitioner declaring to the cosmos their intended engagement with the Work
  across the coming years. It requires committing to a timescale that extends
  beyond the curriculum, beyond any foreseeable personal plans.

  What does it feel like to plan alchemical work across the next two to three
  years? Record honestly: is this liberating, sobering, or both?
]

